    <refsection id="Description_MEAS_Diode">
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            This block models a simple diode. If input voltage (Vin) is greater than a threshold voltage (equals to Vt*Maxexp), 
            output current (Iout) can be computed with the formula:
        </para>
        <para>
            <latex>
                \begin{eqnarray}
                Iout = Ids * (\exp(Maxexp) * (1+\frac{\Large{Vin}}{\Large{Vt}}-Maxexp)-1) + \frac{\Large{Vin}}{\Large{R}}
                \end{eqnarray}
            </latex>
        </para>
        <para>
            In the other case:
        </para>
        <para>
            <latex>
                \begin{eqnarray}
                Iout = Ids * (\exp(Vin/Vt) -1) + \frac{\Large{Vin}}{\Large{R}}
                \end{eqnarray}
            </latex>
        </para>
    </refsection>
